1
00:01:37,320 --> 00:01:39,000
Prince, I'm here.

2
00:01:45,720 --> 00:01:47,360
This man impersonated a guard

3
00:01:47,360 --> 00:01:48,759
and plotted against you.

4
00:01:48,800 --> 00:01:49,479
But,

5
00:01:49,960 --> 00:01:51,600
I've already executed him on the spot.

6
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:52,640
May I ask, Princess,

7
00:01:52,640 --> 00:01:53,479
are you hurt?

8
00:01:53,680 --> 00:01:54,440
I'm fine.

9
00:01:54,440 --> 00:01:55,160
And you?

10
00:01:55,680 --> 00:01:56,479
Hah!

11
00:01:57,920 --> 00:02:00,480
Killing a guard and holding the Princess hostage.

12
00:02:00,480 --> 00:02:02,400
You have some nerve.

13
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:09,600
Lord Hu,

14
00:02:09,720 --> 00:02:10,919
you're finally here.

15
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:12,020
If you hadn't come,

16
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:14,040
the Princess and I would be dead.

17
00:02:16,520 --> 00:02:17,079
It's him.

18
00:02:17,240 --> 00:02:18,720
This man impersonated a guard,

19
00:02:18,720 --> 00:02:20,200
plotting to murder the Princess.

20
00:02:20,200 --> 00:02:21,920
If I hadn't risked my life to protect the Princess,

21
00:02:21,920 --> 00:02:23,079
we would all be done for.

22
00:02:23,079 --> 00:02:23,680
Shut up.

23
00:02:25,079 --> 00:02:26,560
The times are chaotic.

24
00:02:26,960 --> 00:02:28,620
A treasure like the Glass Frog

25
00:02:28,880 --> 00:02:30,480
is best left in your care.

26
00:02:31,160 --> 00:02:32,920
Only by giving the Glass Frog to Lord Hu

27
00:02:32,920 --> 00:02:34,560
can I access the historical evidence.

28
00:02:34,560 --> 00:02:35,820
That way, I can find it.

29
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:36,880
But where exactly did Lord Hu

30
00:02:36,880 --> 00:02:38,680
hide the Glass Frog?

31
00:02:42,520 --> 00:02:43,720
The genuine article.

32
00:02:48,600 --> 00:02:49,480
Leave us.

33
00:02:49,640 --> 00:02:52,440
I have private matters to discuss with the Prince.

34
00:03:03,680 --> 00:03:04,440
Princess,

35
00:03:04,720 --> 00:03:06,180
you are truly courageous.

36
00:03:19,160 --> 00:03:21,200
This is a tradition of our Great Ming.

37
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:21,640
Yes.

38
00:03:22,079 --> 00:03:24,440
It is also the etiquette of Siam.

39
00:03:28,920 --> 00:03:30,850
Why did you give him the Liuli Frog?

40
00:03:31,920 --> 00:03:33,079
To protect you, of course.

41
00:03:33,079 --> 00:03:34,120
To save me?

42
00:03:34,360 --> 00:03:35,320
Then shouldn't you have taken out

43
00:03:35,320 --> 00:03:36,760
your Buluotuo's Tear?

44
00:03:37,560 --> 00:03:38,079
Right.

45
00:03:38,520 --> 00:03:40,650
Technically, I have Buluotuo's Tear.

46
00:03:40,920 --> 00:03:42,640
What if she asks me for it?

47
00:03:43,600 --> 00:03:45,400
You are a Princess of Great Ming.

48
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:46,480
For the sake of the Great Ming,

49
00:03:46,480 --> 00:03:48,610
what does it matter if I marry far away?

50
00:03:49,360 --> 00:03:49,920
Princess.

51
00:03:49,920 --> 00:03:51,280
It is time to depart.

52
00:03:51,920 --> 00:03:52,720
Princess.

53
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:54,400
What is wrong?

54
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:56,120
Kill the Prince. Kill him.

55
00:03:56,120 --> 00:03:57,240
Then you will be free.

56
00:03:57,240 --> 00:04:01,880
Kill him.

57
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:32,320
Long time no see.

58
00:04:34,920 --> 00:04:36,400
We are not.

59
00:04:57,480 --> 00:04:58,480
What did you do?

60
00:04:58,960 --> 00:05:00,360
What did you dream about?

61
00:05:00,440 --> 00:05:01,560
Was it successful?

62
00:05:07,160 --> 00:05:08,420
The Princess saved me.

63
00:05:10,040 --> 00:05:12,360
He entered the virtual space twice in a row.

64
00:05:12,360 --> 00:05:13,220
He's too tired.

65
00:05:27,520 --> 00:05:29,120
Aya, how do you feel?

66
00:05:29,720 --> 00:05:30,960
If it weren't for the Prince,

67
00:05:30,960 --> 00:05:32,020
I would be done for.

68
00:05:32,480 --> 00:05:33,960
The Prince saved me.

69
00:05:41,120 --> 00:05:43,650
The world inside must be wonderful, isn't it?

70
00:05:45,360 --> 00:05:48,020
The Prince and I drove away Marquis Hu together.

71
00:05:48,400 --> 00:05:49,280
And then?

72
00:05:50,520 --> 00:05:51,400
Then?

73
00:05:54,840 --> 00:05:56,170
Where is the Liuli Frog?

74
00:05:57,040 --> 00:05:58,240
The Tear of Buluotuo?

75
00:05:59,520 --> 00:06:01,380
Godfather, let Aya get some rest.

76
00:06:02,520 --> 00:06:03,640
She is exhausted.

77
00:06:08,720 --> 00:06:10,400
Oh, the Prince.

78
00:06:11,560 --> 00:06:13,200
It looks like our little Aya

79
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:16,080
has fallen in love.
